HEADWORD: Epiploce
<hw>E*pip"lo*ce</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.,
connection, from Gr. <?/ a plaiting together, fr. <?/ to plait or braid
in; <grk>'epi`</grk> upon + <?/ to twist, plait.]</ety>
<fld>(Rhet.)</fld> <def>A figure by which one striking circumstance is
added, in due gradation, to another; climax; <it>e. g.</it>, ⟦ldquo⟧He
not only spared his enemies, but continued them in employment; not only
continued, but advanced them.⟦rdquo⟧</def>
<rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

